headline: How The Evolving Price Target Is Rewriting The Story For KeyCorp (KEY)
summary: Why the price target on KeyCorp is shifting now The recent change in price target for KeyCorp has less to do with a single headline and more to do with how analysts are reassessing the story around the bank, from its earnings mix to its balance sheet priorities. With the market rethinking what it wants from regional banks, that updated target reflects a fresh view of KeyCorp's risk, reward and role in an investor's portfolio. headline: TFC Q4 Earnings Beat Despite Y/Y Rise in Expenses, Stock Dips
summary: Truist Q4 adjusted EPS beats estimates. Higher expenses and credit provisions offset gains in NII, fees and loan growth.

headline: KeyCorp (KEY) Stock Trades Up, Here Is Why
summary: Shares of regional banking company KeyCorp (NYSE:KEY) jumped 2.9% in the afternoon session after the company reported strong fourth-quarter results that surpassed Wall Street's expectations and announced a significant share buyback program.

headline: Why First Interstate BancSystem (FIBK) Stock Is Trading Up Today

headline: Why Northwest Bancshares (NWBI) Stock Is Trading Up Today

headline: Zions Stock Rises 1.7% as Q4 Earnings Beat on NII & Fee Income Growth
summary: ZION stock gains 1.7% after Q4 EPS beat estimates, driven by higher net interest income, stronger fee revenue, and modest loan and deposit growth.

headline: Scotiabank Comments on Expected Contribution from KeyCorp's Fourth Quarter Earnings
summary: Scotiabank announced today that the expected net income contribution from its ownership interest in KeyCorp will be approximately CAD $81 million in Q1 2026. This contribution represents the Bank's share of KeyCorp's Q4 2025 net income, includes acquisition-related and other accounting impacts, is net of the Bank's associated funding costs and is reported on a one-month lag.

headline: KeyCorp names new lead independent director
summary: Two other board members will retire at the bank’s annual meeting. Activist investor HoldCo Asset Management sought board changes, among other demands, in a presentation last month.

headline: KeyCorp's Doing Well, But It's Not Enough
summary: KeyCorp's Q4 beat shows margin gains and balance-sheet optimization, but valuation looks rich vs. peers. Click here to read an analysis of KEY stock now.

headline: KEY Q4 Deep Dive: Organic Growth and Strategic Investments Drive Solid Results
summary: Regional banking company KeyCorp (NYSE:KEY) reported Q4 CY2025 results topping the market’s revenue expectations, with sales up 12.5% year on year to $2.01 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $0.41 per share was 6.3% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
